      { question: "How should an error in a handwritten medical record be corrected?", options: ["Use white-out to cover the error and rewrite the correct information", "Draw a single line through the error, write the correction, and add date, time, and initials", "Remove the page and rewrite the entire entry", "Leave the error and add a separate addendum"], correct: 1, rationale: "The proper method for correcting errors in handwritten medical records is to draw a single line through the erroneous entry so it remains legible, write the correct information nearby, and add the date, time, and initials of the person making the correction. Obliterating, removing, or using white-out on medical record entries is never acceptable." }
